                A group of segments to identify and describe costs and
                charges relating to a part or task item.

1920               TCC, Charge/rate calculations
                   To identify one charge related to the part or task
                   item.

1930               IDE, Identity
                   To reference a party to whom this cost or charge
                   relates.

1940               ATT, Attribute
                   To specify coded attributes relating to the cost or
                   charge, such as method of calculation.

1950               MOA, Monetary amount
                   To specify monetary amounts relating to the cost or
                   charge component, such as tax amount, discount
                   amount.

1960               PCD, Percentage details
                   To specify percentages relating to the cost or
                   charge component, such as cost or charge discount
                   percentage.

1970               FTX, Free text
                   To provide text information about the cost or
                   charge component.


1980               Segment group 22: COT-IDE-ATT-MOA-PCD-RFF-FTX
                   A group of segments to identify and describe
                   contribution and recovery details related to the
                   risk object component cost or charge.

1990                  COT, Contribution details
                      To identify one contribution or recovery
                      component relating to the risk object cost or
                      charge.

2000                  IDE, Identity
                      To reference a party to whom this contribution
                      or recovery relates.

2010                  ATT, Attribute
                      To specify coded attributes relating to the
                      contribution or recovery component, such as
                      contribution or recovery status code.

2020                  MOA, Monetary amount
                      To provide monetary amounts relating to the
                      contribution or recovery component, such as
                      contribution or recovery amount.

2030                  PCD, Percentage details
                      To specify percentages relating to the
                      contribution or recovery component, such as
                      percentage of insurer's responsibility.

2040                  RFF, Reference
                      To specify references relating to the
                      contribution or recovery component.

2050                  FTX, Free text
                      To provide text information relating to the
                      contribution or recovery component.


2060   Segment group 23: PRC-IDE-ATT-DTM-MOA-QRS-RFF-FTX
       A group of segments to identify and describe an action relating
       to the claim, such as assessment, financial settlement,
       progress report.

2070      PRC, Process identification
          To identify one action related to the claim.

2080      IDE, Identity
          To reference parties related to the claim.

2090      ATT, Attribute
          To specify coded attributes relating to the action, such as
          assessment report type, manner of settlement.

2100      DTM, Date/time/period
          To specify dates related to the action, such as date of
          report, date inspection to be performed.

2110      MOA, Monetary amount
          To specify monetary amounts related to the action, such as
          settlement amount.

2120      QRS, Query and response
          To provide the response to coded questions about the action.

2130      RFF, Reference
          To specify references related to the action, such as
          instructor's assessment reference, assessor's assessment
          reference.

2140      FTX, Free text
          To provide text information about the action, such as
          progress description, verdict description.


2150   Segment group 24: SEQ-IDE-ATT-DTM-RFF-SG25
       A group of segments to describe the previous insurance history
       for the risk associated with this claim. The previous insurance
       is expressed as a sequence of periods of insurance.

2160      SEQ, Sequence details
          Identifies the sequence of this period of previous
          insurance.

2170      IDE, Identity
          To reference parties related to this period of insurance
          history.

2180      ATT, Attribute
          To specify coded attributes relating to the previous
          insurance history, such as policy class.

2190      DTM, Date/time/period
          To specify dates relating to the period of insurance
          history, such as inception date, expiry date.

2200      RFF, Reference
          To specify references relating to the period of previous
          insurance history, such as policy number.


2210      Segment group 25: COD-IDE-ATT-DTM-MOA-QRS-RFF-FTX
          A group of segments to identify and describe components
          relating to the period of previous insurance history, such
          as prior loss.

2220         COD, Component details
             To identify one prior loss that relates to the period of
             previous insurance.

2230         IDE, Identity
             To reference party numbers for the prior loss as
             specified by the intermediary, insurer and client.

2240         ATT, Attribute
             To specify coded attributes relating to the prior loss,
             such as loss type, incident type.

2250         DTM, Date/time/period
             To specify dates relating to the prior loss, such as loss
             date, settlement date.

2260         MOA, Monetary amount
             To specify monetary amounts relating to the prior loss,
             such as loss amount.

2270         QRS, Query and response
             To specify the response to coded questions relating to
             the prior loss.

2280         RFF, Reference
             To specify references for the prior loss, such as
             insurer’s historical claim reference.

2290         FTX, Free text
             To provide free text about the prior loss, such as prior
             loss description.

